title: Common English Vocabulary Words that Start with G

json.text: Welcome to PnT English channel. A learning vocabulary with videos channel.
Welcome to the oxford 3000 essential words program. Now, let's start learning English!
Section 7: Words Starting with G. g. g . g. g in this case is a written abbreviation
of gram or grams. A metric unit of weight equal to one thousandth of a kilogram. 400g
flour. gain. g . a . i . n . gain. gain means obtain
or a quantity that is added. Gain pleasure from one's garden.
gallon. g . a . l . l . o . n . gallon. gallon means United States liquid unit equal to 4
quarts or 3.785 liters. The car does about 50 miles per gallon .
gamble. g . a . m . b . l . e . gamble. gamble means take a risk in the hope of a favorable
outcome. When you buy these stocks you are gambling.
gambling. g . a . m . b . l . i . n . g . gambling. gambling means the act of playing for stakes
in the hope of winning (including the payment of a price for a chance to win a prize). His
gambling cost him a fortune. game. g . a . m . e . game. game means a single
play of a sport or other contest. The game lasted two hours.
gap. g . a . p . gap. gap means a conspicuous disparity or difference as between two figures.
Gap between income and outgo. garage. g . a . r . a . g . e . garage. garage
means an outbuilding (or part of a building) for housing automobiles. A house with a built-in
garage. garbage. g . a . r . b . a . g . e . garbage.
garbage means food that is discarded (as from a kitchen). Don't forget to take out the garbage.
garden. g . a . r . d . e . n . garden. garden means a plot of ground where plants are cultivated.
Children playing in the garden . gas. g . a . s . gas. gas means any substance
like air that is neither a solid nor a liquid. the state of matter distinguished from the
solid and liquid states. Air is a mixture of gases.
gasoline. g . a . s . o . l . i . n . e . gasoline. gasoline means a volatile flammable mixture
of hydrocarbons (hexane and heptane and octane etc.). An oil refinery serves to make gasoline
from crude oil. gate. g . a . t . e . gate. gate means a movable
barrier in a fence or wall. This house has a beautiful gate.
gather. g . a . t . h . e . r . gather. gather means assemble or get together. Gather some
stones. gay. g . a . y . gay. gay means bright and
pleasant; promoting a feeling of cheer. A gay sunny room.
gear. g . e . a . r . gear. gear means a toothed wheel that engages another toothed mechanism
in order to change the speed or direction of transmitted motion. Careless use of the
clutch may damage the gears. gene. g . e . n . e . gene. gene means a segment
of DNA that is involved in producing a polypeptide chain; it can include regions preceding and
following the coding DNA as well as introns between the exons; it is considered a unit
of heredity. Genes were formerly called factors. general. g . e . n . e . r . a . l . general.
general means applying to all or most members of a category or group. Comprehensible to
the general reader. generally. g . e . n . e . r . a . l . l . y
. generally. generally means usually; as a rule. Generally it doesn't rain much here.
in general. in general. in general means without distinction of one from others.he is interested
in snakes in general. generate. g . e . n . e . r . a . t . e . generate.
generate means bring into existence. The new manager generated a lot of problems.
generation. g . e . n . e . r . a . t . i . o . n . generation. generation means all
the people living at the same time or of approximately the same age. My generation have grown up
without the experience of a world war. generous. g . e . n . e . r . o . u . s . generous.
generous means willing to give and share unstintingly. A generous donation.
generously. g . e . n . e . r . o . u . s . l . y . generously. generously means in
a generous manner. He gave generously to several charities.
gentle. g . e . n . t . l . e . gentle. gentle means soft and mild; not harsh or stern or
severe. A gentle reprimand. gently. g . e . n . t . l . y . gently. gently
means in a gradual manner. A gently sloping terrain.
gentleman. g . e . n . t . l . e . m . a . n . gentleman. gentleman means a man of refinement.
Thank you-you're a real gentleman. genuine. g . e . n . u . i . n . e . genuine.
genuine means not fake or counterfeit. A genuine Picasso.
genuinely. g . e . n . u . i . n . e . l . y . genuinely. genuinely means in accordance
with truth or fact or reality. A genuinely open society.
geography. g . e . o . g . r . a . p . h . y . geography. geography means study of the
earth's surface; includes people's responses to topography and climate and soil and vegetation.
A degree in geography. get. g . e . t . get. get means come into
the possession of something concrete or abstract. She got a lot of paintings from her uncle.
get on. get on. get on means have smooth relations. My boss and I get on very well.
get off. get off. get off means leave a vehicle, aircraft, etc. We'll try and get off straight
after lunch. giant. g . i . a . n . t . giant. giant means
any creature of exceptional size. of great mass; huge and bulky. A giant jet.
gift. g . i . f . t . gift. gift means something acquired without compensation. Thank you for
your generous gift. girl. g . i . r . l . girl. girl means a young
woman. The baby was a girl. girlfriend. g . i . r . l . f . r . i . e
. n . d . girlfriend. girlfriend means any female friend. Mary and her girlfriend organized
the party. give. g . i . v . e . give. give means cause
to have, in the abstract sense or physical sense. She gave him a black eye.
give away. give away. give away means make a gift of. She gave away her antique furniture.
give out. give out. give out means give off, send forth, or discharge; as of light, heat,
or radiation, vapor, etc. Can you give the drinks out, please?
give up. give up.give up means give up with the intent of never claiming again. She gave
up her children to her ex-husband when she moved to Tahiti.
glad. g . l . a . d . glad. glad means showing or causing joy and pleasure; especially made
happy. Glad that they succeeded. glass. g . l . a . s . s . glass. glass means
a brittle transparent solid with irregular atomic structure. I cut myself on a piece
of broken glass. glasses. g . l . a . s . s . e . s . glasses.
glasses means optical instrument consisting of a pair of lenses for correcting defective
vision. I broke one of the arms of my glasses when I was playing basketball.
global. g . l . o . b . a . l . global. global means involving the entire earth; not limited
or provincial in scope. Global monetary policy. glove. g . l . o . v . e . glove. glove means
the handwear used by fielders in playing baseball. A pair of gloves.
glue. g . l . u . e . glue. glue means cement consisting of a sticky substance that is used
as an adhesive. join or attach with or as if with glue. They glue the sign on the wall.
gm. g . m . gm. gm is a written abbreviation for gram.a metric unit of weight equal to
one thousandth of a kilogram. A weight of approximately 100 grams.
go. g . o . go. go means change location; move, travel, or proceed. How fast does your
new car go? go down. go down. go down means move downward
and lower, but not necessarily all the way. The temperature is going down.
go up. go up. go up means move upward. The smoke went up from the forest fire.
be going to. be going to. be going to means to intend or be about to start often used
as an alternative future construction.what's going to happen to us?
goal. g . o . a . l . goal. goal means the state of affairs that a plan is intended to
achieve and that (when achieved) terminates behavior intended to achieve it. The winning
goal came with less than a minute left to play.
god. g . o . d . god. god means the supernatural being conceived as the perfect and omnipotent
and omniscient originator and ruler of the universe. The Son of God .
gold. g . o . l . d . gold. gold means a chemical element. Made from or covered with gold. The
gold dome of the Capitol. good. g . o . o . d . good. good means having
desirable or positive qualities especially those suitable for a thing specified. When
she was good she was very very good. good at. good at. good at means able to do
something well. Nick has always been good at finding cheap flights.
good for. good for. good for means having a useful or helpful effect on someone or something.
The experience was good for her. goodbye. g . o . o . d . b . y . e . goodbye.
goodbye means a farewell remark. They said their goodbyes.
goods. g . o . o . d . s . goods. goods means things that are produced to be sold. Increased
tax on goods and services. govern. g . o . v . e . r . n . govern. govern
means bring into conformity with rules or principles or usage; impose regulations. We
cannot govern the way people dress. government. g . o . v . e . r . n . m . e
. n . t . government. government means the organization that is the governing authority
of a political unit. The government reduced taxes.
governor. g . o . v . e . r . n . o . r . governor. governor means the head of a state government.
The former governor of the colony. grab. g . r . a . b . grab. grab means take
hold of so as to seize or restrain or stop the motion of. Grab the elevator door!
grade. g . r . a . d . e . grade. grade means a body of students who are taught together.
Early morning grades are always sleepy. gradual. g . r . a . d . u . a . l . gradual.
gradual means proceeding in small stages. A gradual increase in prices.
gradually. g . r . a . d . u . a . l . l . y . gradually. gradually means in a gradual
manner. The snake moved gradually toward its victim.
graduate. g . r . a . d . u . a . t . e . graduate. graduate means receive an academic degree
upon completion of one's studies. She graduated in 1990.
grain. g . r . a . i . n . grain. grain means a small hard particle. A grain of sand.
gram. g . r . a . m . gram. gram means a metric unit of weight equal to one thousandth of
a kilogram. Health experts recommend no more than 6 grams of salt each day.
grammar. g . r . a . m . m . a . r . grammar. grammar means the branch of linguistics that
deals with syntax and morphology. I have a batch of grammar tests to mark by tomorrow,
so I can't go out tonight. grand. g . r . a . n . d . grand. grand means
of behavior that is impressive and ambitious in scale or scope. In the grand manner.
grandchild. g . r . a . n . d . c . h . i . l . d . grandchild. grandchild means a
child of your son or daughter. Mary loves her grandchild.
granddaughter. g . r . a . n . d . d . a . u . g . h . t . e . r . granddaughter. granddaughter
means a female grandchild. The old woman really brightened up when she saw her granddaughter.
grandfather. g . r . a . n . d . f . a . t . h . e . r . grandfather. grandfathermeansthe
father of your father or mother.His grandfather was a professor.
grandmother. g . r . a . n . d . m . o . t . h . e . r . grandmother. grandmother means
the mother of your father or mother. My grandmothers are both widows.
grandparent. g . r . a . n . d . p . a . r . e . n . t . grandparent. grandparent means
a parent of your father or mother. My grandparents live in Japan.
grandson. g . r . a . n . d . s . o . n . grandson. grandson means a male grandchild. My grandson's
birthday was on Monday. grant. g . r . a . n . t . grant. grant means
let have or allow. Grant permission. grass. g . r . a . s . s . grass. grass means
narrow-leaved green herbage: grown as lawns; used as pasture for grazing animals; cut and
dried as hay. He made a sign to me to keep off the grass.
grateful. g . r . a . t . e . f . u . l . grateful. grateful means feeling or showing gratitude.
Grateful for the tree's shade. grave. g . r . a . v . e . grave. grave means
a place for the burial of a corpse. He put flowers on his mother's grave.
gray. g . r . a . y . gray. gray means of an achromatic color of any lightness intermediate
between the extremes of white and black. The little grey cells.
great. g . r . e . a . t . great. great means relatively large in size or number or extent;
larger than others of its kind. A great juicy steak.
greatly. g . r . e . a . t . l . y . greatly. greatly means to an extraordinary extent or
degree. He improved greatly. green. g . r . e . e . n . green. green means
of the color between blue and yellow in the color spectrum; similar to the color of fresh
grass. A green tree. grocery. g . r . o . c . e . r . y . grocery.
grocery means a marketplace where groceries are sold. The grocery store included a meat
market. groceries. g . r . o . c . e . r . i . e . s
. groceries. groceries means a plural form of grocery. There are many groceries in this
town. ground. g . r . o . u . n . d . ground. ground
means the solid part of the earth's surface. The plane turned away from the sea and moved
back over ground. group. g . r . o . u . p . group. group means
several people or things that are all together in the same place. A group of children.
grow. g . r . o . w . grow. grow means become larger, greater, or bigger; expand or gain.
The problem grew too large for me. grow. g . r . o . w . grow. grow up means
become an adult. Children grow up so quickly. growth. g . r . o . w . t . h . growth. growth
means the process of an individual organism growing organically. He proposed an indicator
of osseous growth in children. guarantee. g . u . a . r . a . n . t . e . e
. guarantee. guarantee means a pledge that something will happen or that something is
true. There is no guarantee that they are not lying.
guard. g . u . a . r . d . guard. guard means a person who keeps watch over something or
someone. A security guard. guess. g . u . e . s . s . guess. guess means
expect, believe, or suppose. I guess she earned a lot of money with her new novel.
guest. g . u . e . s . t . guest. guest means a visitor to whom hospitality is extended.
He owns a magnificent mansion on an enormous estate and even has three guest cottages for
visitors. guide. g . u . i . d . e . guide. guide means
someone who shows the way by leading or advising. be a guiding force, as with directions or
advice. The teacher guided the gifted students towards the more challenging courses
guilty. g . u . i . l . t . y . guilty. guilty means responsible for or chargeable with a
reprehensible act; or marked by guilt. Guilty of murder.
guitar. g . u . i . t . a . r . guitar. guitar means a stringed instrument usually having
six strings; played by strumming or plucking. Eric Clapton has played lead guitar for a
number of different bands over the years. gun. g . u . n . gun. gun means a weapon that
discharges a missile at high velocity. Bang! You're dead, cried the little girl as she
pointed her toy gun at her brother. guy. g . u . y . guy. guy means an informal
term for a youth or man. A nice guy. Thanks for watching! This is all for section
7: Words starting with G. You can move on to section 8 : Words starting with H. We'll
see you next time. Goodbye!
